<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76575" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-745x497.jpg" alt="Rau Honda CB900F café racer by HB-Custom" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
<span class="lede">Upgrading your suspension</span> and brakes is a hassle-free way to eke more handling performance out of your motorcycle. But if you have the time and money, why not go the whole hog? This <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/tag/honda-cb900" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Honda CB900F</a> from HB-Custom in Germany sports several upgraded parts—but its biggest drawcard is its race-bred Rau frame.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re not familiar, Manfred Rau was a German frame builder who started making performance motorcycle frames in 1972. His designs took cues from the work of Egli and Bimota, with a focus on Japanese engines.<span id="more-76564"></span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76567" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-745x497.jpg" alt="Rau Honda CB900F café racer by HB-Custom" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-1.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Needless to say, Rau frames aren&#8217;t easy to come by&#8230; which is exactly why Holger Breuer (the &#8216;HB&#8217; in <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/tag/hb-custom" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HB-Custom</a>) had to find one for his latest project. “The client is a very good friend of mine and it&#8217;s the second bike that we&#8217;ve built together,” he tells us. “The goal was to build something really special with more or less no budget restrictions.”</p>
<p>“The first bike that I built for him was a BMW—but the whole custom BMW thing has become kind of boring. The goal was to follow a new direction; a four-cylinder engine instead of a boxer, a Honda instead of a BMW, and a very unique frame.”</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76568" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-745x497.jpg" alt="Rau Honda CB900F café racer by HB-Custom" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-2.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Some deft hunting by Holger produced a 1977 Rau frame and a Honda CB900F of unknown vintage. The engine was yanked out of the CB and rebuilt to the tune of 1,062 cc. Peek inside, and you&#8217;ll find rebored cylinders and a set of forged Mahle pistons.</p>
<p>This Rau Honda CB900F also benefits from a set of Mikuni RS36 carbs, fed by a custom-made carbon fiber airbox to comply with Germany&#8217;s stringent regulations. Without any cam- or crankshaft fettling, it now pushes out close to 100 hp. A digital ignition and hydraulic clutch add modern reliability.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76569" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-745x497.jpg" alt="Rau Honda CB900F café racer by HB-Custom" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-3.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Since the Rau frame that was sourced for this project was designed for the CB900F motor, bolting the latter into the former was a mere formality. To complete the rolling chassis, Holger added the forks and yokes from a Suzuki GSX-R1000 K7 up front and installed a Wilbers shock at the back. A Wilbers steering damper was fitted too, for extra front-end stability.</p>
<p>The stunning 17” wheels are custom-built items from the German wheel specialists PVM. They&#8217;re wrapped in Pirelli Diablo Supercorsa tires and stopped by an assortment of Yamaha R1 and R6 braking components.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76570" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-745x497.jpg" alt="Rau Honda CB900F café racer by HB-Custom" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-4.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Holger only used the Honda CB900F&#8217;s engine, which meant that he had to create everything else from scratch. For the bodywork, he manipulated sheets of aluminum to form a new fairing, fuel tank, and humped tail section. The bike&#8217;s new lines borrow ideas from both <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/tag/cafe-racer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">café racer</a> and vintage race bike aesthetics, with a few hard edges to echo the CB&#8217;s DNA.</p>
<p>A generous cutout on the right side of the fuel tank offers a view of the Rau frame&#8217;s distinctive backbone. Take a closer look, and you&#8217;ll also spot a handmade &#8216;fuel gauge.&#8217;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76571" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-745x497.jpg" alt="Rau Honda CB900F café racer by HB-Custom" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-5.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
The sleek fairing wears an MRA windshield and hosts an LED headlight from Koso. The taillight&#8217;s from Highsider, and the turn signals are Kellermann items. Tucked away in the cockpit are a Motogadget speedo and RFID ignition receiver, with Gilles Tooling clip-ons, Magura levers, and Highsider switches.</p>
<p>Gilles Tooling rear-set foot pegs are mounted lower down, as are numerous carbon fiber and drilled parts. A custom license plate bracket sits out back, while a burly four-into-one exhaust from Schüle adds the final touch.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76573" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-745x745.jpg" alt="Rau Honda CB900F café racer by HB-Custom" width="745" height="745" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-745x745.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-420x420.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-768x768.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-380x380.jpg 380w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-90x90.jpg 90w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-1200x1200.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-360x360.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-720x720.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-275x275.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7-150x150.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/rau-honda-cb900f-7.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Wrapped in a dark teal livery with subtle black graphics, HB-Custom&#8217;s Rau Honda CB900F has a subdued look that belies just how wild it is. We could stare at it for ours—and we can only imagine how glorious it must sound at full tilt.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.hb-custom.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HB-Custom</a> | <a href="https://www.instagram.com/__hbcustom__/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a> | Images by Emayat Wahab</p>
